cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with ensuring eventual consistency of optimistically replicated trees in a distributed system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper focuses on designing Conflict-free Replicated Data Types (CRDT) for tree data structures. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper deals with shared data in a distributed system. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes different policies for resolving concurrency problems in tree data structures, which can be useful for distributed application programmers. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a new method for ensuring eventual consistency using CRDTs, which can be seen as a programming language construct.
